article.linkText: Tyson puts up 22, Belmont downs Northern Iowa 90-70
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- — Cade Tyson had 22 points in Belmont's 90-70 victory over Northern Iowa on Wednesday night. Tyson had eight rebounds for the Bruins (5-3, 1-0 Missouri Valley Conference). Ja'Kobi Gillespie scored 18 points and added three steals. Malik Dia was 7 of 15 shooting (1 for 4 from 3-point range) to finish with 16 points. The Panthers (2-5, 0-1) were led by Trey Campbell, who recorded 13 points. Michael Duax added 12 points for Northern Iowa. In addition, Tytan Anderson had eight points and eight rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
